{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Raise the age to 18 for receiving Disability Living Allowance",
        "additional_details": "There\u2019s many things you aren\u2019t able to do at 16: playing the lottery, smoking and drinking alcohol. Would you allow a 16 year old to do this no we wouldn\u2019t. 16 is just to young to take on the complexity of filling out many forms to claim a sickness benefit which is what the family would rely on. It\u2019s simple: raise claiming PIP up to 18 so there\u2019s no pressure on 16 year olds to become adults way to fast.",
        "background": "Being 16 is still considered a child in the UK so how can a 16 year old take the responsibility of applying for PIP and to be knowledgeable about finances. To fill in complex forms is overwhelming for an adult let alone a 16 year old. You can\u2019t drink alcohol until 18 so the laws should be the same.",
